location.address: A32, 34, 36, Jalan 1/116B, Kuchai Enterpreneurs’ Park, 58200 Kuala Lumpur

tip.text: Cappuccino overdone. Felt burned and the gooey gooey rich chocolate brownie is way too sweet. Should be rich Sugar brownie than chocolate. Like eating a block of sugar. Sorry folks at GravyBaby.
High end adventure clothing and bag packs. Not cheap but great quality. Staffs know their things.
Crews are very helpful and professional during our trip to Rinjani! May want to come here again.
Nice pool! However they have regular electrical trips. What a bummer. Overall the resort is ok. Quiet and nice.
Best diving company here at Gili. Staffs are very professional.
Impressed by the hall. Look at their flooring!
Nice hall! Not too hot.
Yummy food! Don't forget to order the "Don"!

venue.name: Sanpoutei Ramen 三宝亭らーめん

tip.text: It is a little pricey. But they serve the freshest sashimi. Friendly people and service is good.
Reasonably priced. Food are fresh and the taste is good. I rate this place 7/10.
Newest Branch in KL. The future of luggages is with Rimowa.
Clean Pool, the size is ok. Love the seats, it is super comfy. Can really doze off.
Prefer to swim at night. Not many people and very quiet. During the Day time it will get hot around 12:30pm.

formattedAddress: Kuala Lumpur, Federal Territory of Kuala Lum

tip.text: Duck Confit Pasta is the bomb! Well "oiled" with chilies and it is not over powering. You should order them before the cakes.

formattedAddress: Lot K138, First Floor, Suria KLCC
location.address: Lot K138, First Floor, Suria KLCC

tip.text: One of the hidden treasures in Terrenganu. Very peaceful. Hotel staffs are very friendly. Some of them work as singers at the bar in the evening. Nice swimming pool and the food is good.

venue.name: Summer Bay Lang Tengah Island Resort

formattedAddress: 29, Tingkat Bawah (Jalan Tengku Ampuan Zabedah B 9/B)

tip.text: Nice friendly place. They offer croissant that is amazingly delicious. Cappuccino and pistachio cake would be a great combination to finish off your afternoon.
Nice cappuccino. Great place to hangout. At least there is a place worth visiting in oug.
Utterly disgusted with the food here. Most of the feedbacks in Foursquare are negative. This place is going down soon. I'm sorry and really sad to see that the food of its quality becoming like this.
The food is not up to my standard despite spending 2k for dinner. Manager showing faces and not friendly. Only person that serves us well was the lady that handle our room. Utterly disappointed.
Love their Pizza. Overall service was good. Lambshank was great and their naan taste great.
Be early. Long queue expected to wait at least an hr for a table. 11pm onwards is the best time to go if you want to avoid waiting for so long. Clam and hokkien Mee is a must!
The broth is good. Personally I prefer the one with haruan fish. Fried. Service is fast. I hope they give more ingredients. I'm satisfied.
They only serve dinner for a limited time period within the week. Food is good. Love their vegetarian tapas #cappuccino not bad too.
Friendly staff and nice place for coffee.
Coffee is good, but please don't serve in glass cups. It doesn't retains heat as good as coffee cups. Not practical at all.
Try their salad. This place is seriously underrated. But keep it that way so I can enjoy the peace while dining and eating with my friends.
Curry noodles is a must. Add spare ribs! The soup is thick! Yummy.
Nice ambience but it didn't match the food served. Was disappointed with the service. I'm sorry.
Small bowl orders taste better than big ones. If you want to add more of the mince pork, it's RM2 extra btw.
Salted Caramel Chocolate cake is good. Just nice. Apparently their cotton ball is a must try. I had my usual cappuccino. Well it's alright. Love their ambience. I Rate this place 8/10.
The staffs are all very friendly and nice. Been here for decades. Bangsar may be posh but their prices are very reasonable. Excellent service.
Great value and friendly staff. Newly opened, you get complimentary watercress soup and herb jelly for desserts. 10%off everything until June 2015. Enjoy and have a great 2015.

venue.name: Village Roast Duck 乡村烧鸭

tip.text: Cappuccino taste moderately ok. However I must say that their tau fu fah cheesecake is a must to order here. Soft, silky smooth with a hint of ginger. One think I don't like is why close at 7pm?

formattedAddress: Block 5 (Unit 12-1), Jalan Jalil Jaya 6 (Jalil Link, Jalan Jalil Jaya 6,)

tip.text: Great blend from Gayo, Ratawali. Love the cappuccino here. Slight taste of chocolate and a hint of nuts and apricot. Rating 8/10.

location.address: Lot 1A, 83-95 Level UG1, Publika, Jalan Dutamas 1

tip.text: Love their interiors. A little small but it is very intimate. Better then other performing Art Centers in KL.

location.address: H-01, DPAC, Empire Damansara,  Jalan PJU 8/8, Damansara Perdana

tip.text: Love their blend of cappuccino. Cakes not bad too. It's nice to come at night to enjoy the peace and quiet. Great place for dates too.

formattedAddress: G-25, Empire Damansara, Jalan PJU 8/8, Damansara Perdana
location.address: G-25, Empire Damansara, Jalan PJU 8/8, Damansara Perdana

tip.text: Should try their signature Big bone. Soup is different from their normal BKT soup. However it is limited to 20 pcs a day!

formattedAddress: Hokkien Association Hall, Jln Batu Tiga Lama
location.address: Hokkien Association Hall, Jln Batu Tiga Lama

tip.text: Best pork noodle in town! Asked for upsize with mince meat and not sliced meat. It taste much better.

venue.name: Restoran Makanan Sun Sea (山海茶餐室)

tip.text: One of the best tasting Prawn Noodle ever! Soup stock is tantalizing. Ingredients are fresh and "healthy".

venue.name: River South (Hoe Nam) Prawn Noodles 河南肉骨大蝦面

tip.text: Portions are small. Taste wise is good. Price 6/10, taste 8/10. Overall value 7/10.

formattedAddress: Empire Shopping Gallery, LG32, Jalan SS16/1
location.address: Empire Shopping Gallery, LG32, Jalan SS16/1

tip.text: Great ambience, good environment for a chat, a casual date or small business discussion. Food are reasonable, good value on lunch set meals. Coffee needs a lot of improvement especially cappuccino.

formattedAddress: Kuala Lumpur City Center Level 1, Menara 2 Petronas (Persiaran KLCC Kuala Lumpur)
location.address: Kuala Lumpur City Center Level 1, Menara 2 Petronas

tip.text: A different way of enjoying your usual Magnum Ice Cream. It is very filling. Be warned that it is a sin to eat Alone. ❤️
The must try is grilled Crabs and Seafood porridge. Both are made to perfection. Crabs for lunch! how about that. Fresh ones too. I rate the quality of food 8/10. Place 6/10. Price 8/10. Reasonable!
One of the best chicken rice ball in Melaka. Lesser oil, less msg compared to the ones in jonker.
Have to order a bottle of drink to go up to the helipad. Great for dates and a good chat. However it can be better if they have soft music on top.
A little packed. Upstairs is smokey and if you want to irritate the smoker, I suggest you smoke a cigar! 👍😝
Thai fried rice and clear tom yum soup will complete your meal. Be early if not the staff will chase you out as soon as 3pm is approaching. Enjoy your meal.
Hangar steak are huge and good enough to share with a friend. Try their rums.
Friendly staffs! Their beef cheeks is a must over here. Top it with a bottle of wine.
Should try their Turkish tea. The lamb is amazing!
It is pricier than Sutera Harbor, but good service. Rooms and facilities is better. They have an huge swimming pool.

formattedAddress: The Magellan Sutera Resort (1 Sutera Harbour Boulevard, Sutera Harbour)

tip.text: Hotel staffs are friendly but slow at times. Food is okay. Rooms are clean and of good value. Nice scenery and clean beach.

formattedAddress: The Pacific Sutera Hotel (1 Sutera Harbour Boulevard)

tip.text: Coconut pudding and Sabah Vegy is a must. Other than that cultural dance to entertain you. Seafood is overrated and expensive. I rate them 7/10.
One of the best Peranakan food in Melaka. Aunty Amy is still at it serving people with her cooking even it is partially handled by her son.
Christmas Season is here! Jason's have good varieties of cookies and chocolate for sale.
Great place to hangout! Always packed and full of people. Get the Madonna blend.
Chocolate Souffles are to die for. And not forgetting hot chocolate drink to go with it!!!

formattedAddress: #01-11, The Pier @ Robertson (80 Mohamed Sultan Rd.)

tip.text: Great place for dates, good view. It is refreshing. Don't forget about the sunset too. At night the lights surrounding the area is beautiful.
A breath of fresh air compare to the old LCCT. Nice mall, ample place to eat and they have a grocery market too. The terminal reminds me of Adelaide Airport.
Pavillion best kept secret. Not as crowded as Illys at the front entrance. Nice Sofa, great selection of coffee. Do try their Cappuccino Vienna. And enjoy the big Victoria Secret TV Screen.
I usually drink Cappuccino. If you happen to be here at Pasarbella, do drop by and have a taste of their coffee. Their Latte is good too. It is a must try! Don't forget to order some dutch pancakes!

formattedAddress: Stall #67/68 PasarBella @ The Grandstand (200 Turf Club Rd.)

tip.text: Come here during weekends, don't miss the yummy Dutch pancakes near Dutch colony coffee. On Saturdays, if you are lucky, there is a live blue fin tuna cutting at 7pm at the seafood area.
Nice selection of Japanese food. The service is ok. Can be very noisy during peak hour. The staffs sometimes ignore your request during peak hrs. Nevertheless the food here are generally ok.
The best people to intoxicate you with their Whiskey knowledge. Don't drink and drive.

venue.name: Fine Spirits by La Maison du Whisky

tip.text: If you have not been to Orchard Rd in Singapore. You must come! Great place to shop, walk and people watch.
This wagyu beef bowl is the best! orgasmic! Just show it to the chef and they will know what to do. My personal favorite. If you plan to get "lucky" with your love one.. Feed him/her this. ❤️👍
Loved the selection of crab meal. Fresh and huge. Reasonably priced. One Crab per plate.
Personally I love the cappuccino. Cakes and desserts can be better. Overall on coffee 7.5/10. Desserts 6.5/10. Staff service 8.5/10, cosy factor 8.5/10.
Cappucino is just alright. What can be improved on is the service time where it took the barista 15mins to make 2 cups of coffee when the place has less than 5 customers. Super slow...
Just make sure you make a reservation before you come. Seats are super limited and take them long time to prepare their dish. Pork Knuckles however is da bomb.

tip.text: Coffee, Salads , cake is good. Don't go for proper meals. Ordered medium rare steak they give me well done. Ordered chicken and the meat is still cold. Disappointed.
Soft shell Spagetinni!
Best Onden!
Be early! Most roasts will be finished before 1.30pm. Try their Char Siew and Roast Pork...and Duck!
They have the best ramen in town. The Pork is thick and tasty. Slurps...

tip.text: One of the most crowded and popular Store in London.
Best popcorn in town. I go for caramel crisp anytime.Reasonably priced too.

tip.text: Nice place and ambience. Staffs needs to be trained. They dont know the food well. Seriously the staffs will make the place look bad. Overall I rate the food and place 8.5/10. Staff 6.5/10.
Super Long Que, Not worth the time. Food is okay. I would rate it 8/10.
